Regarding the &quot;offline-directline&quot; package, it isn&#39;t out-of-date. My suspicion there is you are not configuring it correctly. This following code sample is enough to get the package running. Then you just need to point your bot to it.

```js
const directline = require(&#39;offline-directline&#39;);
const express = require(&#39;express&#39;);

const app = express();

directline.initializeRoutes(app, 4000, &quot;http://127.0.0.1:3978/api/messages&quot;);
```

If you continue to struggle, another option is the &quot;browser bot&quot; which you can find on the Botbuilder-Samples repo [here](https://github.com/microsoft/BotBuilder-Samples/tree/master/samples/javascript_es6/01.browser-echo). In this setup, the bot is hosted entirely within the browser and does not require using Direct Line. Setup is only slightly different and will require you to play with configurations some, as a result. But, it&#39;s worth a look.

Hope of help!

